issue.title: User remove product ray
issue.body:
* **The Name of this branch is**
UserRemoveProduct_ray

* **Please check if the PR fulfills these requirements**
- [ ] All files contain comments including Author, Purpose
- [ ] All methods contain comments including Purpose, And Argument List and a short purpose for each argument
- [ ] Tests for the changes have been added (for bug fixes / features)
- [ ] Docs have been added / updated (for bug fixes / features)



* **What kind of change does this PR introduce?** (Bug Fix, Feature, Document Update...)

A logged in user should now see a "My Products" on the nav bar when logged in
When the user clicks on the My Products, they should see a list of their products with a delete affordance
when the user clicks on the delete affordance, and confirms the delete action the product should be removed from the system

* **What Ticket is associated with this PR**
#20 


* **What is the new behavior?**  (if this is a feature change)
Not a feature change - see above

* **List all core functionality** 
UserProductVIewModel - this is the model used to display the products to the user
ProductsController.MyProducts() - this method finds the products created by the current user and returns the view of the UserProductViewModel

MyProducts.chtml - this is the razor template using the UserProductsViewModel
_MyProductsPartial.chtml - this is the nav bar item rendered when a user logs in



* **Other information / Steps to Test**:

1. git fetch 
1. git checkout UserRemoveProduct_ray
1. run program
1. log in as a user  that has product (or create some product if you don't have any) 
1. you should see a "My Products" link on the navbar
1. click on that link and verfy you have products
1. these products should only be the products for YOU and no other user
1. click on the delete affordance on an item. 
1. confirm you want to delete and delete it 
1. you should be returned to the my products list and the product you deleted should be gone.

issue.title: User add product to sell ray
issue.body:
* **The Name of this branch is**

UserAddProductToSell_ray
* **Please check if the PR fulfills these requirements**
- [x] All files contain comments including Author, Purpose
- [x] All methods contain comments including Purpose, And Argument List and a short purpose for each argument
- [x] Tests for the changes have been added (for bug fixes / features)
- [x] Docs have been added / updated (for bug fixes / features)



* **What kind of change does this PR introduce?** (Bug Fix, Feature, Document Update...)
Feature - A user can now add a product to sell once they are logged in

* **What Ticket is associated with this PR**

#2 

* **What is the new behavior?**  (if this is a feature change)
NA - new feature - not a change

* **List all core functionality** 

ProductsController.cs - scaffolding added by EF. 
ProductsController.Create(Product product) This method creates a product given user input and returns a user to the detail view of that item they created
Views/Shared/_Layout.cshtml - injected razor partials once user is logged in
Views/Shared/_SellProductPartial - The razor template for the sell a product nav bar entry



* **Other information / Steps to Test**:
1. Git fetch
1. Git checkout UserAddProductToSell_ray
1. in visual studio launch the project
1. when the web application shows the home page verify that the "Sell A Product" affordance in the nav bar is not viewable
1. Click the log in button and log in
1. Verify the "Sell a Product" affordance is now viewable
1. Click the "Sell a product" affordance on the nav bar. 
1. You should be brought to the Create product view
1. First click the sell button to verify that it does not create a product without all required fields. 
1. Fill in all required fields EXCEPT for the price field. 
1. In the price field attempt to enter a word instead of a price. 
1. try clicking sell - the price field should show you need to enter a number
1. erase the word you put in price and replace it with a valid number i.e. 9,95
1. click the sell button
1. You should be brought to a detail view of the product you just created
